properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 16 at 2:58PM CST until February 18 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...Snow Expected Monday Afternoon and Evening...

.A low pressure system will bring accumulating snow to the region
Monday afternoon. Some mixed precipitation and icing will be
possible by Monday evening. This will likely impact the Monday
evening commute.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations
of 3 to 5 inches and ice accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Portions of central, east central and northeast
Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From noon Monday to midnight CST Monday night.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...This system will be primarily snow through
the afternoon. Mixed precipitation and ice formation become more
likely in the evening and early overnight hours.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON MONDAY TO MIDNIGHT CST MONDAY NIGHT
